<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-178-368  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 178 368.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Wall Street Journal  Feb 27 1990 pB4(W) pB4(E) 16 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Broadcasters urged to try fiber optics as alternative to satellitetransmission. (Technology)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lopez, Julie Amparano.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Bell Communications Research Inc (Bellcore) is developing a fiberoptic network for use by television broadcasters to transmit theirlive television programs underground.andP;  ABC is testing the fiberoptic network for three months; subsequently, NBC, CBS, Fox andPBS will take turns to test the network for three months at atime.andP;  Bellcore is attempting to prove to broadcasters that theland-based network will result in a better quality picture atlower costs than the traditional satellite transmission.andP;  Qualitysatellite transmission is also dependent on positive weatherconditions.andP;  Bellcore's ulterior motive is to spur interest infiber optic networks on behalf of its owners, the seven regionalBell holding companies.andP;  Such large clients as the broadcastcompanies would improve the profile of fiber optics.andP;  Broadcastershave been reluctant to use fiber optics because switching andcontrol equipment was never sophisticated enough.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bellcore Bell Communications Research Inc. (research).andO;Topic:     Fiber opticsNew TechniqueCommunications TechnologyNetworks.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>